  "prompt": "What is an interface icon?",
  "response": "An interface icon is a small graphical symbol or image used in digital user interfaces (UI) to represent a specific function, action, feature, or type of content. These icons help users quickly understand and interact with an application, website, or software by providing visual cues and shortcuts. Interface icons are designed to be simple, recognizable, and intuitive, typically using minimal details and clear shapes to communicate their purpose effectively.\n\nExamples of interface icons include:\n1. Menu/hamburger icon\n2. Home icon\n3. Search icon\n4. Settings/gear icon\n5. Share icon\n6. Play/pause buttons\n7. Download icon\n8. Delete/trash icon\n9. Refresh/reload icon\n10. Messaging/chat icon\n\nThese icons are commonly found in mobile apps, desktop applications, websites, and other digital platforms to enhance user experience and navigation.",
